Singer Timaya has urged fans to be wary as he lamented the scourge of ritual killings by youths who are carried away by the get-rich-quick syndrome. The “Dem Mama” singer in a tweet was reacting to the report of the actions of three teenage boys caught burning the head of a girl said to be in a relationship with one of them for money ritual in Oke Aregba, Abeokuta, Ogun State. Many Nigerians on social media described the gruesome actions of the teenagers as “despicable and callous”.   OAP tongue lashes Portable for insulting Kenyan ladies     Celebration of untraceable wealth feeds monsters- Noble Igwe     Eight female celebrities who committed suicide   In his reaction, the ‘Egbebripapa 1 of Bayela’ said it’s dangerous outside and people need to be vigilant as a supposed buddy could decide to use one for ritual. - Advertisement - “17 years old boys doing money ritual?? Innocent humans killed for money, even your own homeboy can use you. “Watchout guys, it’s really Cold Outside,” he tweeted.